  "context": "14 administrative personnel or even from other agencies/entities with the prescribed workload as follows:\n\nTable VI.4 Teaching Overload for Lecturers\n\n| Human Resource | Workload |\n|---|---|\n| 1. faculty without administrative designation | maximum of 10 teaching hours overload or as followed by their respective PSGs in a semester across programs |\n| 2. faculty with administrative designation (regardless of release hours) | maximum of 6 teaching hours overload in a semester across programs |\n| 3.regular administrative personnel | maximum of 6 teaching hours in a semester across programs |\n| 4. administrative support staff-COS | maximum of 15 teaching hours in a semester |\n| 5. government- employed VL (part- time) | maximum of 15 teaching hours/or as allowed by the mother agency in a semester across programs |\n| 6. privately employed VL (part- time) | Maximum of 15 teaching hours/or as allowed by the mother agency in a semester across programs |\n\nSection 24 The maximum number of teaching hours for lecturers shall likewise be stretched reasonably in special case(s) when the number of units handled and the corresponding teaching hours could not be reduced nor split (Illustration: 12 units + additional 4-unit course=16 units equivalent to 16 teaching hours). Section 25 The following shall be compensated for the teaching services rendered via asynchronous mode of delivery, while on official travel, provided that the conditions set have been satisfied:",
